{"name":"Archon Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 32\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum WIS 9</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS and CHA</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 10</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any, including shields </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common, </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Beast, Elemental, Elf, Fey</span></p>\n<p>Archons are high elf servants of the primal powers—elementals, beast lords, and demiurges—who first bestowed wisdom upon the elven race. Archons do not worship these beings, but instead honour ancient pacts of mutual assistance and protection, from which an archon’s arcane power stems.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ArchonProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"450\" /></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"JqmOQ4e2JwUkLvIV"}
{"name":"Assassin Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 62\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: None</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: DEX</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p>\n<p><strong>Armour</strong>: Leather, no shields</p>\n<p><strong>Weapons:</strong> Any except two-handed <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">melee weapons</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Assassins are humans trained to murder efficiently. They use stealth and deception to get close to targets so they can deliver a quick, killing blow with either a melee weapon or well- placed shot with a missile. Their specialised skills are not well-suited for dungeon crawls or wilderness exploration, but assassins do thrive in urban environments where they may be hired as “equalisers” in matters of political intrigue, turf wars, and commercial subterfuge.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/AssassinProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"551\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"uu7VP2BEISmhUWyP"}
{"name":"Barbarian Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 38\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum DEX 9, maximum WIS 15</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">STR</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">1d10</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">14</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any non-plate, including </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">shields (see below)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any (see below) </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Common, Tribal tongue</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Barbarians are stout humans who form tribal societies in a specific “home” terrain (q.v., Appendix F). They live by foraging, hunting, herding, and basic farming, yet have intricate clan hierarchies, laws, customs, and social taboos. Devoted to nature worship, they view divine magic as proof of the primordial gods’ favour, but arcane magic is anathema. Barbarians do not like cities and do not welcome outsiders.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/BarbarianProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"548\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"SVxgxJmnq6A95bGZ"}
{"name":"Bard Progression","content":"<p><strong style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Requirements</strong><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">: Minimum DEX 9, minimum WIS 9</span></p>\n<div title=\"Page 64\">\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">CHA</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">1d4</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">14</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Leather, no shields </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Weapons: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any one-handed melee or </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">missile weapons</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common, +2 </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">additional</span></p>\n<p>Bards are human warrior-poets who chronicle the exploits of daring adventures as participants. They relate these histories through song and verse, which are lent credibility as eyewitnesses to the events described in their epics. Between adventures, bards earn a living by entertaining others with tales of adventure—in fact, adventuring parties sometimes hire bards to enhance their heroic reputations (perhaps, it is imagined, with a liberal application of flatter- ing embellishment).</p>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/BardProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"550\" /></p>\n<p> </p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"bgH1jMrKrxvX51SL"}
{"name":"Beast-talker Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 40\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum DEX 9, minimum STR 13</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">WIS</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">1d6</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">14</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Leather, no shields </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any (see below) </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common</span></p>\n<p>Beast-talkers are humans raised in animal totem or zoolatry-based societies, or perhaps even by animals themselves. At home in the wilds, beast-talkers create a sanctuary for beasts to live in safety, away from settled areas. As implied, they can communicate with animals, who perceive beast-talkers as animals themselves; within their home range, beast-talkers are recognised as alphas by all but the most aggressive and territorial beasts.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/Beast-TalkerProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"559\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"dVm9fhiHP4AHmvQ8"}
{"name":"Berserker Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 42\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: None</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: STR</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d8</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p>\n<p><strong>Armour</strong>: Leather or furs, including <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">shields</span></p>\n<p><strong> Weapons</strong>: Any, except missiles (see class abilities<span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">)</span></p>\n<p><strong> Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common</p>\n<p>Berserkers are human fighters dedi- cated to an animal totem or beast cult. Berserker “clans” model themselves along the social habits and hierarchies of their totem animal. In clan or tribal cultures, berserkers may mimic their animal’s behaviour, sleep cycles, diet, and living condi- tions to form a more intimate bond with the beast’s spirit; in more “advanced” societies, berserkers may observe such traits only symbolically.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/BerserkerProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"551\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"wY0pmrYRHOarB46w"}
{"name":"Crusader Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 18\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum STR 9</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any, including shields </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any permitted by their </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">order</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">A cleric sub-class, crusaders are human warrior-priests of religious fighting orders. Such orders are auxiliary and subordinate to their par- ent church or sect, whose mission they support through force of arms. Com- mon to all orders is an “infidel,” or the primary target of its martial attention, which could be as specific as a pagan tribe or rival sect, or as broad as beings of an opposing race, nation, or alignment. Not all churches support fighting orders, nor are all orders truly subordinate.</span></p>\n<p>N.B. As self-righteous fighters with limited clerical ability, crusaders are a good template for paladin (or anti-paladin) archetypes in settings where the struggle between good and evil is foundational and epic. In settings where alignment struggles are not the focus of conflict—where the line between good and evil is blurred and subjective—crusaders can occupy a more multifaceted niche if referees exploit each fighting order’s history, mission, and bias to create moral grey areas.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/CrusaderProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"556\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"cEIPOcY6gF3SIL3c"}
{"name":"Elder Progression","content":"<p> </p>\n<div title=\"Page 26\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CON 9, minimum WIS 9</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">WIS</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">1d6</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">12</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any, including shields </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Weapons: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any permitted by their </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">deity (see below)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common, </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Dwarfish, Gnome, Goblin, Kobold</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Elders are dwarf clerics, dedicated to dwarven immortal powers. Elders renounce their home clan when they take up the faith, joining a clerical clan dedicated either to an individu- al deity or (in smaller settlements) the entire dwarf pantheon.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ElderProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"496\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"fkghDiMLVdaTgVsh"}
{"name":"Necromancer Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 54\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Maximum CHA 12</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: INT</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d4</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">None</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Dagger only </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Languages: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Necromancers are human magic-users fascinated with the cycle of life and death, studying the positive and negative energies associated with each to re-animate the dead or create life anew. Not surprisingly, their scholarship is perceived as unnatural, and they are shunned and mistrusted as a result.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/NecromancerProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"552\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"R5YB5qByKLLVPUuW"}
{"name":"Scout Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 66\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum STR 9</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: DEX</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any non-plate, no shields </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any except two-handed </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">melee weapons</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common</span></p>\n<p>Scouts are humans who’ve adapted to life in the wilderness, working to keep stretches of untamed territory safe for travellers and local populations. Scouts know their territory well—both its terrain and its denizens—warding it against foes that might pose a danger to local settlements. They believe that birds, beasts, and plants have as much a right to life as “civilised” peoples and try to ensure the peace and safety of all—they’re just as likely to run down poachers as to guide peaceful travellers safely through a dark forest.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ScoutProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"555\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"oxx9y9W5flHDMKCW"}
{"name":"Shaman Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 20\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CON 9</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: WIS</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d6</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Leather, no shields </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any one-handed melee </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">A shaman is a tribal cleric common to barbarian and nomadic cultures. They revere animal spirits as exem- plars of proper outlook and conduct in all matters.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/ShamanProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"553\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"EozCgjZEkiOz69CM"}
{"name":"Sorcerer Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 56\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CHA 9</p>\n<p><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: INT</p>\n<p><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: 1d4</p>\n<p><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: 14</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">None</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Weapons</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Dagger only </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Languages</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Alignment, Common</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Sorcerers are human magic-users who derive their spell casting ability from pacts with one or more powerful extra-planar patrons.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/SorcererProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"557\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"qsEfjZXOTNttMURY"}
{"name":"Warden Progression","content":"<div title=\"Page 48\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong>: Minimum CON 9, minimum DEX 9</p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Prime Requisite</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">DEX and STR</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Hit Dice</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">1d6</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Maximum Level</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">8</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\"><strong>Armour</strong>: </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Any appropriate to size, </span><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">including shields</span></p>\n<p><strong>Weapons</strong>: Any appropriate to size <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">(see Combat ability)</span></p>\n<p><strong> Languages</strong>: Alignment, Common, <span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">Halfling</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family:var(--font-primary);font-size:var(--font-size-14)\">These halfling “outdoorsmen” patrol the wilderness surrounding a halfling community against threats and mis- chief. Wardens work at the pleasure of the local sheriff and thus share responsibility for the community’s safety and defence.</span></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><img src=\"modules/bx-options/img/WardenProgression.png\" width=\"600\" height=\"393\" /></p>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"PxqQojdX3Ghz8Uq5":3},"flags":{"cf":{"id":"temp_u7oz7ynetg","path":"BX Options Progressions","color":"#000000"}},"_id":"LUeCA9Zkdn4Xyy6X"}
